# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Tabby's voice  —  optional, but it makes her talk like a real cat.
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Tabby speaks through a free OpenAI-compatible LLM. Groq is the fastest
#  free option. Without a key she still runs perfectly — she just falls back
#  to built-in offline lines instead of freshly generated ones.
#
#  To give her a voice:
#    1. Make a free account ....  https://console.groq.com
#    2. Create an API key .......  https://console.groq.com/keys
#    3. Copy this file to ".env"   (remove the ".example")
#    4. Replace the placeholder below with your key, then save.
#
#  start_mascot.bat creates this .env for you automatically on first run.
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------

GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_PASTE_YOUR_FREE_KEY_HERE
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# Only change this if you use a non-Groq OpenAI-compatible provider:
# GROQ_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
